explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the feasibility of implementing an electronic screening tool for patient-reported outcomes (PROs) in an HIV clinic to assess medication adherence and related factors. It does not mention or involve any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models, nor does it discuss any of the listed keywords related to machine learning, deep learning, or large language models. The study is primarily a clinical implementation research using logistic regression for statistical analysis, which is not covered by the provided keywords.
